## 6) Application structure

A conventional organization works well for this project:

```
src/
├─ pages/              # Route-level screens, one file per page
│  ├─ Index.tsx        # "Início"
│  ├─ Historia.tsx     # "História"
│  ├─ Galeria.tsx      # "Galeria"
│  └─ CodigoConduta.tsx# "Código de Conduta"
├─ components/         # Reusable UI (navigation, cards, dialogs, etc.)
│  └─ ui/              # shadcn-ui components (installed via components.json)
├─ assets/             # Images and static imports used by components
├─ lib/                # Small utilities, helpers, constants
├─ styles/             # Optional global CSS modules or additional Tailwind layers
├─ App.tsx             # App composition and routes
└─ main.tsx            # React root creation and bootstrapping
```

* **`pages/*`** map to the public sections documented in the README:

  * **Início**: quick intro and highlights for next events and social links
  * **História**: short narrative with selected historical photos
  * **Galeria**: grid of photos of past events, often opened in a modal for context
  * **Código de Conduta**: core values with an official policy link
    These four areas are explicitly defined in the project description. ([GitHub][1])

* **`components/*`** holds shared UI like the navigation bar, footer, buttons, cards, and any layout primitives. The presence of **`components.json`** at the root indicates **shadcn-ui** was set up to scaffold accessible, Tailwind-styled components into `src/components/ui`. ([GitHub][1])

* **Styling** is driven by **Tailwind CSS**, configured by `tailwind.config.ts` and `postcss.config.js` at the root. ([GitHub][1])

